        public Logger(java.nio.file.Path filePath,
              java.lang.String loggerFileName,
              LogLevel ll)
        This constructor uses basic string representations of system file paths and file name to interpret where the log is to be placed and named.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Examples: "C:\\temp\\" or "/var/log/temp/"; defaults to the Java project directory
        fileName - The name of the log file; it will automatically have a .log extension appended. Defaults to the caller's class name.
        LogLevel - The minimum log level of messages to be logged.
